comments: Kispert (WAS) makes contact to Giddey's (OKC) arm and affects his driving shot attempt.
Kuzma (WAS) briefly loses control of the ball during his drive before regaining it and continuing his dribble.
Kuzma (WAS) and Dort (OKC) engage and disengage with one another while Kuzma sets the pick to force the switch.
Harrell (WAS) could be deemed to be imminently exiting the lane within three seconds.
Caldwell-Pope (WAS)  makes marginal contact to Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) back while rebounding.

Robinson-Earl (OKC) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Caldwell-Pope (WAS) and marginal contact occurs as he briefly rests his left hand on Caldwell-Pope's back. Following this contact, Caldwell-Pope makes incidental contact with Robinson-Earl's right foot as he plants his own right foot to defend the drive.
Caldwell-Pope (WAS) briefly grasps Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) left arm as he defends the drive.
Harrell (WAS) places his right hand momentarily on Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) left arm and applies a stayed left hand to his back that does not affect his driving shot attempt.
Caldwell-Pope (WAS) establishes himself in a legal screening position in the path of Dort (OKC) and absorbs the oncoming contact.
Bazley (OKC) makes incidental contact with Kuzma's (WAS) right hand after the release that does not affect his jump shot attempt.
Robinson-Earl (OKC) and Harrell (WAS) both extend for the rebound and marginal contact occurs as Robinson-Earl's left arm rests over Harrell's right arm.
Harrell (WAS) and Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) engage and disengage with one another during the rebound.
Robinson-Earl (OKC) establishes himself in a legal screening position in the path of Dinwiddie (WAS) and absorbs the oncoming contact.

Kuzma (WAS) contests Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) driving shot attempt and marginal contact occurs when he brushes Gilgeous-Alexander's head with his right forearm. Contact to an opponent?s head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.

Caldwell-Pope (WAS) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Dort (OKC) and marginal contact occurs as the two engage and disengage. Following this contact, Caldwell-Pope twice re-establishes screening position in the path of Dort and marginal contact occurs both times as the two engage and disengage.
Dort (OKC) establishes himself in a legal screening position in the path of Caldwell-Pope (WAS) during the inbound and marginal contact occurs as the two engage and disengage.
Bazley (OKC) commits an intentional foul on Kuzma (WAS).
Robinson-Earl (OKC) makes contact to the ball in Dinwiddie's (WAS) hands and marginal contact occurs to Dinwiddie's left arm as he passes the ball.
Wiggins (OKC) commits an intentional foul on Kuzma (WAS).
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) is in the paint for less than three seconds as an intentional foul is imminent.
Caldwell-Pope (WAS) cleanly deflects Giddey's (OKC) pass following the rebound.
Muscala (OKC) and Hachimura (WAS) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Giddey (OKC) takes fewer than three steps after he has gathered the ball for the driving shot attempt.
